abstract: It’s been hard to find a successor to Carmen Fariña with the skills to run the country’s largest district and a mind-set compatible with the mayor’s.
snippet: It’s been hard to find a successor to Carmen Fariña with the skills to run the country’s largest district and a mind-set compatible with the mayor’s.
lead_paragraph: It is arguably the highest-profile job in elementary and secondary education: chancellor of the New York City school system, with its 1.1 million students and $31 billion annual budget. And yet, two months after Mayor Bill de Blasio announced that Chancellor Carmen Fariña would retire, the spot remains unfilled.

abstract: DreamYard Prep was part of the city’s program for low-performing schools. Now it has been deemed a Rise school, and over time the intensive support will wane.
snippet: DreamYard Prep was part of the city’s program for low-performing schools. Now it has been deemed a Rise school, and over time the intensive support will wane.
lead_paragraph: DreamYard Preparatory high school in the Bronx has spent the last five years on the kinds of lists schools would rather avoid. First, it was a Priority School, a distinction New York bestows on the lowest-performing schools in the state. Then it became a Focus school, which is for schools that are struggling, if not quite so badly. It has also been part of Mayor Bill de Blasio’s Renewal Schools program, which aims to turn around troubled schools using extra resources, rather than just shutting them down.

abstract: Mayor Bill de Blasio will create a commission to recommend changes to the City Charter — and he wants it to strengthen campaign finance laws.
snippet: Mayor Bill de Blasio will create a commission to recommend changes to the City Charter — and he wants it to strengthen campaign finance laws.
lead_paragraph: Mayor Bill de Blasio will use the first State of the City address of his second term to announce a plan to change the City Charter as a way to improve the city’s campaign finance system.
